{"id":28996,"date":"2019-05-09T18:36:53","date_gmt":"2019-05-09T14:36:53","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=28996"},"modified":"2023-08-29T17:52:54","modified_gmt":"2023-08-29T13:52:54","slug":"parable-mathl-bakhil-munfiq","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/09\/parable-mathl-bakhil-munfiq\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Charity: Parable of the spender and miser of charity"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>The parable of the miser and the spender is that of two men clad in armor from their chests to their collars. As for the spender, he does not spend but that it extends or broadens over his skin until it covers the tips of his hands and feet. As for the miser, he does not want to spend anything but that every ring contracts in its place; he tries to loosen it, but it will not.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1443, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1021<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Muttafaqun Alayhi<\/strong><\/em> (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0645\u064e\u062b\u064e\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0628\u064e\u062e\u0650\u064a\u0644\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0646\u0652\u0641\u0650\u0642\u0650 \u0643\u064e\u0645\u064e\u062b\u064e\u0644\u0650 \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u06